<h2 id="lost-little-critters">2: Lost Little Critters</h2>

<h3 id="descripcin-general-1">Descripción general</h3>
<ul>
  <li>A <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nonviolent_video_game">non-violent</a><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nonviolence">¹</a>, 2D platforming game where a group of three mythical creatures —a Unicorn, a Tarand, and a Hippaelectron— try to find their way home after being lost in early 19th century Britain. They journey through the land while working together, taking advantage of each of their unique abilities, avoiding magic hunters who want to keep them for their collections, and making friends along the way. Rated E/E+10, for PC and consoles.</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="mecnicas-1">Mecánicas</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Descripción mecánicas principales (Se debe complementar con bocetos propios, imágenes y/o video de otros productos como juegos, animaciones, películas, etc)</li>
  <li><a href="https://bestiary.ca/beasts/beast140.htm">Unicorns</a><a href="https://bestiary.ca/beasts/beast165.htm">¹</a> -&gt; Abilities according to mythology?</li>
  <li><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hippalectryon">Hippalektryon</a><a href="https://www.summagallicana.it/lessico/h/hippalektryon%20ippogallo.htm">¹</a><a href="https://www.theoi.com/Ther/Hippalektryon.html">²</a><a href="https://bestiary.ca/beasts/beast477.htm">³</a></li>
